Sadtu in Eastern Cape wants schools to be shut down. The union is concerned about ablution facilities, shortage of personal protection equipment and water supply in schools. Both parties are expected to meet tomorrow to discuss the concerns. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG -The SA Democratic Teachers’ Union (Sadtu) in the Eastern Cape wants schools to shut down. The union is concerned about ablution facilities, shortage of personal protection equipment and water supply at schools. COVID-19: Staff at Eastern Cape hospital fear for their lives It’s expected to meet with the education on Tuesday to discuss its concerns. "Even the issue of water that has been promised to be delivered, water tanks -- they have not been delivered as promised,” said provincial secretary, Chris Mdingi. Sadtu says it will meet with the provincial education department on a way forward. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.